climbs.name: Two all beef patties on a sesame seed bun

content.description:
Work your way up through the blank middle of the face with friction moves and tiny crimpy things. 

  Its a rare Iowa Slab climb.
content.protection: After you lead Ronald you can top rope this one.
content.location: It runs up the middle of the face.

content.description: Lead the crack on the right side of the arch.   Its pretty crumbly, and then exit it with a jug to the right of the crack which is usually muddy.  You want to put in a lot of gear before you make the crux move, and make sure that your belayer isn't going to get kabonged with the rock you knock loose.
content.protection: tricams, and cams. Set a sling on the tree that is centered over the arch.
content.location: This is the crack that goes up the right side of the arch.

content.description: Its an arched shaped crack about twenty feet tall.
